metadata.name: City Pop - AI Study II #191
metadata.description:
City Pop takes you to a lively and geometric city created by digital architects. The use of shapes, colors, and lines causes visionary hallucinations leading the viewer to imaginary places filled with endless possibilities.

This project is a generative art experiment using a Text2Code workflow. The JavaScript code for this project was written entirely by AI using GPT-3. None of the code was altered or created by a human aside from changing Math.random() with fxrand().

Text2Code study #2 /// Project CoDexter by @BrainArtLabs

metadata.name: breken #18
metadata.description:
breken is a continued exploration of solid lines and primary colors.

I start with a random set of seed locations. Cracks spread out from these locations until reaching the edge of the square, or encountering another crack. The resulting polygons are then potentially scaled, rotated, and/or warped.

metadata.name: Color of life #65
metadata.description:
console.log("Hello world")

After many thoughts about life, about our relationship as individuals in a society I always bring myself the same doubt, does life become only what we do? Or can we, humans, be personalities without being defined by our professions?

This piece comes from this reflection, when I say that I work with art made with code they soon think that I am an unemployed bum. This work represents the colors that in round and elongated shapes abstract my relationship between code and art, putting beauty in continuous lines, and many times confusing in a general context.

PS: Press [S] to save a png :)
